## [1.12.0-alpha] - 2026-03-02

### ROM Analysis Tools (Sprint 30)

#### Added
- **ROM analysis** (`--rom-info [FILE]`): analyze a loaded ROM to extract hardware
  vectors (RESET, NMI, IRQ), map JSR/JMP targets, detect ASCII strings, and compute
  region usage statistics (code vs data vs fill bytes)
- **`rom_analysis_t`** structure: vectors, subroutine targets (up to 512), strings
  (up to 256), usage statistics
- **`rominfo_init()`**, **`rominfo_analyze()`**, **`rominfo_report()`**,
  **`rominfo_report_to_file()`**, **`rominfo_find_pattern()`** API
- **Pattern search**: find arbitrary byte sequences in ROM with address results
- **Sorted target map**: JSR/JMP targets sorted by address with reference counts
- **10 new ROM analysis tests**: init, vector detection, JSR targets, JMP targets,
  string detection, pattern search, usage stats, report output, empty ROM, cross-refs
- **`make test-rominfo`** target in Makefile

#### Changed
- **main.c**: `--rom-info` option, analysis runs after ROM load, output to stdout or file

## [1.11.0-alpha] - 2026-03-02

### CPU Performance Profiler (Sprint 29)

#### Added
- **CPU performance profiler** (`--profile FILE`): track per-address execution counts,
  cycle hotspots, and opcode frequency distribution. Writes a summary report on exit.
- **`cpu_profiler_t`** structure with 64K address space coverage (hits + cycles per address)
- **`profiler_init()`**, **`profiler_start()`**, **`profiler_stop()`**,
  **`profiler_record_instruction()`**, **`profiler_record_cycles()`**,
  **`profiler_reset()`**, **`profiler_report()`**, **`profiler_report_to_file()`** API
- **Report format**: summary stats, top 20 hotspots by execution count, top 20 by cycle
  usage, full opcode frequency histogram
- **10 new profiler tests**: init, start/stop, record instruction, address hotspots,
  opcode histogram, cycle tracking, report output, inactive no-op, reset, invalid file
- **`make test-profiler`** target in Makefile

#### Changed
- **emulator.h**: added `cpu_profiler_t profiler` field and `#include "utils/profiler.h"`
- **main.c**: profiler integration in emulation loop (record before + after cpu_step),
  report generation on exit

## [1.10.0-alpha] - 2026-03-02

### CPU Trace Logging (Sprint 28)

#### Added
- **CPU trace logging** (`--trace FILE`): log every CPU instruction with
  disassembly and full register state to a file for debugging and analysis
- **`--trace-max N`**: limit trace to N instructions (default: unlimited)
- **`cpu_trace_t`** structure in `emulator_t` for trace state management
- **`trace_init()`**, **`trace_open()`**, **`trace_attach()`**,
  **`trace_log_instruction()`**, **`trace_close()`**, **`trace_set_max()`** API
- **Trace output format**: `CYCLES  PC  BYTES  DISASM  A=XX X=XX Y=XX SP=XX P=XX`
  (one line per instruction, human-readable)
- **10 new CPU trace tests**: init, open/close, invalid file, attach, log instruction,
  multiple instructions, max count, register state, inactive no-op, cycle count
- **`make test-trace`** target in Makefile

#### Changed
- **emulator.h**: added `cpu_trace_t trace` field and `#include "utils/trace.h"`
- **main.c**: trace integration in emulation loop (before `cpu_step`), CLI parsing,
  trace cleanup on exit

## [1.9.0-alpha] - 2026-03-02

### Display Scaling (Sprint 27)

#### Added
- **Display scaling** (`--scale N`): integer scale factor 1 to 4 for pixel-perfect
  rendering. Default scale remains x3 (720x672). Scale x1 = 240x224, x2 = 480x448,
  x4 = 960x896.
- **F3 hotkey**: cycle display scale (x1 → x2 → x3 → x4 → x1) at runtime
- **`renderer_set_scale()`**: change scale dynamically (resizes window, re-centers)
- **`renderer_get_scale()`**: query current scale factor
- **`renderer_cycle_scale()`**: advance to next scale factor
- **Nearest-neighbor scaling**: `SDL_HINT_RENDER_SCALE_QUALITY` set to "0" for
  crisp pixel-perfect upscaling (no blurring)
- **10 new display scaling tests**: screen dimensions, window sizes at x1/x2/x3/x4,
  headless renderer init, scale factor validation, framebuffer size, pixel pitch,
  video init
- **`make test-renderer`** target in Makefile

#### Changed
- **renderer.c**: added `current_scale` state, `renderer_set_scale()`,
  `renderer_get_scale()`, `renderer_cycle_scale()` functions
- **main.c**: `renderer_init()` now uses CLI `--scale` value instead of hardcoded 3
- **Version**: 1.8.0-alpha → 1.9.0-alpha
- **Test count**: 216 → 226 (10 new renderer tests)

## [1.8.0-alpha] - 2026-03-02

### MCP-40 Plotter Emulation (Sprint 26)

#### Added
- **MCP-40 4-color pen plotter** (`src/io/mcp40.c`, `include/io/mcp40.h`):
  full command parser (H=Home, D=Draw, M=Move, J=Color, P=Print, I=Init,
  L=LineType, Q=CharSize) with 480x400 RGB framebuffer and BMP export
- **Bresenham line drawing** with 5 dash pattern types (solid, 4 dashed)
- **Built-in 5x7 bitmap font** (95 printable ASCII glyphs) for P command
  with scalable character size (Q command, 1-63x)
- **4 pen colors**: black (0), blue (1), green (2), red (3)
- **Command chaining**: multiple commands in one line (e.g. `J1M50,50D100,50`)
- **Multi-coordinate support**: draw polylines in single D/M command
- **Printer type routing**: `oric_printer_type_t` enum (PRINTER_NONE, PRINTER_TEXT,
  PRINTER_MCP40) routes Centronics bytes to text file or MCP-40 parser
- **CLI `--printer-type TYPE`**: select printer mode (`text` or `mcp40`)
- **Auto BMP export**: plotter output exported on close if dirty
- **10 new MCP-40 unit tests**: init, home, move, draw line, color, multi-coords,
  print char, line type, BMP export, command chaining
- **`make test-mcp40`** target in Makefile

#### Changed
- **printer.h/printer.c**: added `oric_printer_type_t` enum, `mcp40_t` field,
  MCP-40 routing in `oric_printer_check_strobe()`, auto-set type to PRINTER_TEXT
  on `oric_printer_open()` if type is PRINTER_NONE
- **Version**: 1.7.0-alpha → 1.8.0-alpha
- **Test count**: 206 → 216 (10 new MCP-40 tests)

## [1.7.0-alpha] - 2026-03-02

### Centronics Printer Emulation (Sprint 25)

#### Added
- **Centronics printer interface** (`src/io/printer.c`, `include/io/printer.h`):
  captures LPRINT/LLIST output to a text file via VIA Port A data + CA2 STROBE
- **STROBE detection**: monitors VIA PCR CA2 mode transitions (forced low → forced
  high) to detect Centronics handshake, matching real hardware protocol
- **CLI `-p` / `--printer FILE`**: capture all printer output to the specified file
- **Automatic flush**: output flushed on newline/carriage return for real-time viewing
- **10 new printer unit tests**: init state, open/close, single byte, string output,
  disabled mode, strobe sequence validation, CA2 bit extraction, flush, reopen, LPRINT
  simulation
- **`make test-printer`** target in Makefile

#### Changed
- **Version**: 1.6.0-alpha → 1.7.0-alpha
- **Test count**: 196 → 206 (10 new printer tests)

## [1.6.0-alpha] - 2026-03-02

### IJK Joystick Support (Sprint 24)

#### Added
- **IJK joystick interface** (`src/io/joystick.c`, `include/io/joystick.h`):
  emulates the most common ORIC joystick adapter, read via PSG Port A
  (register 14), active low. Bit layout: 0=Left, 1=Right, 3=Down, 4=Up, 5=Fire
- **Keyboard-as-joystick mode** (`--joystick keys`): arrow keys + Right Ctrl/Alt
  as fire button. Joystick events consume keyboard events to avoid conflicts
- **SDL2 game controller mode** (`--joystick gamepad`): full SDL2 game controller
  support with D-pad, left stick (8000 dead zone), and A/B/X buttons as fire.
  Supports hot-plug detection
- **Joystick/keyboard blending**: PSG Port A callback returns keyboard AND
  joystick state (both active low), allowing simultaneous use
- **SDL_INIT_GAMECONTROLLER**: renderer init now includes game controller
  subsystem for joystick support
- **CLI `-j` / `--joystick MODE`**: `keys` for keyboard-as-joystick, `gamepad`
  for SDL2 controller
- **10 new joystick unit tests**: init state, disabled mode, press/release
  directions, fire button, simultaneous presses, release all, IJK bit layout,
  mode switching, all four directions, reset
- **`make test-joystick`** target in Makefile

#### Changed
- `emulator_t`: added `oric_joystick_t joystick` field
- `keyboard_matrix_read()`: blends keyboard AND joystick via `oric_joystick_read()`
- SDL2 event loop: dispatches controller/joystick events, keyboard-as-joystick
  consumes arrow keys before keyboard handler
- `renderer_init()`: SDL_Init now includes `SDL_INIT_GAMECONTROLLER`
- Version updated from 1.5.0-alpha to 1.6.0-alpha

#### Tests
- 196 tests via `make tests` (186 existing + 10 new), 100% pass rate

